    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Corbin Carroll** leads the charge with an elite 85.94 score, serving as our cornerstone play against Sean Burke. The math is heavily in his favor: beyond the favorable park factors and the platoon advantage, the projection accounts for a \"Slow SP Delivery\" tag, which significantly enhances his stolen base potential\u2014a critical factor for our strategy. Similarly, **James Wood** (76.28) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) provide massive upside. **James Wood** benefits from the leadoff spot against a favorable matchup, while **Mickey Moniak** is positioned perfectly to capitalize on a platoon advantage against Randy V\u00e1squez, with park factors inflating his scoring projection by 14%.\n\nThe most difficult personnel decision involved **Giancarlo Stanton**, who finished just outside the starting cut with a 48.48 score. While his raw power remains a constant threat, the optimizer ultimately benched him because he faces Connelly Early, whose 2.34 xERA acts as a significant drag on our efficiency goals. We opted for the higher floor offered by **Trevor Story** (74.11) and **Brice Turang** (73.15), both of whom are projected to feast on pitchers with xERAs above 4.40. We are also keeping a close eye on **Dalton Rushing**; his 51.31 score is tempered by a 35% rain risk, and as a lineup-pending asset, his final value will remain volatile until the official card is posted. Our bench depth\u2014including **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Max Muncy**\u2014stands ready should any late lineup scratches occur, but for now, we are prioritizing the high-speed, high-matchup efficiency of our current starters to maintain our edge in the steals category.",
